# Portfolio Website

A personal portfolio site deployed on Vercel, serving as the entry point / link hub for various projects.

## Architecture

- **Portfolio** (`mywebsite.com`, `www.mywebsite.com`) — static/SSG Next.js site on Vercel.
- **Projects** — each hosted independently (Vercel, VPS, Cloudflare Pages, etc.) and reachable via its own subdomain (`project.mywebsite.com`). The portfolio links out to them; it does not proxy them.
- **DNS** — Cloudflare (host-agnostic, CNAME flattening at apex, easy per-subdomain routing).

## Stack

- Framework: Next.js (deployed via Vercel Git integration)
- Language: TypeScript

## Per-project subdomain pattern

Each project gets its own `<name>.mywebsite.com` DNS record pointing at wherever that project is hosted. Adding a project = add DNS record + add a card/link on the portfolio page. Projects are fully independent.

## Coding conventions

- See @AGENTS.md for Next.js conventions
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional React components only
